1
00:00:20,280 --> 00:00:21,560
[Monday, January 18, 1593]

2
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,040
[11:18 a.m.]

3
00:01:45,617 --> 00:01:46,840
Let's go.

4
00:02:12,490 --> 00:02:13,491
My brother.

5
00:02:14,430 --> 00:02:15,431
My brother.

6
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,160
Today’s battle

7
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:25,000
shall be told for generations to come.

8
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:33,120
But regardless of the legends told,

9
00:02:35,480 --> 00:02:37,280
only I

10
00:02:40,137 --> 00:02:42,000
understand your inner thoughts.

11
00:02:49,277 --> 00:02:52,360
In 1563,

12
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:55,560
King Bayinnaung of Hongsawadi

13
00:02:56,360 --> 00:02:59,440
leads his grand armada to lay siege to Phitsanulok,

14
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:01,597
at that time,

15
00:03:02,197 --> 00:03:04,841
a sovereign city-state under the crown of Ayutthaya.

16
00:03:07,640 --> 00:03:10,600
King Maha Thammaracha of Phitsanulok

17
00:03:11,090 --> 00:03:12,521
could no longer withstand the onslaught.

18
00:03:13,763 --> 00:03:17,960
With no reinforcements arriving from Ayutthaya,

19
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:22,840
he was forced to swear fealty to King Bayinnaung

20
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:26,320
to save his city,

21
00:03:27,770 --> 00:03:31,640
and was compelled to lead his own men to join the Hongsawadi army

22
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:34,680
in the invasion of Ayutthaya.

23
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:39,440
Ayutthaya fell.

24
00:03:41,370 --> 00:03:44,320
Both Ayutthaya and Phitsanulok

25
00:03:44,997 --> 00:03:47,200
were reduced to vassal states,

26
00:03:47,337 --> 00:03:49,040
bound in subjection to Hongsawadi

27
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:51,840
from that day forth.

28
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:13,000
[1564 A.D. - Chan Royal Palace, Phitsanulok]

29
00:05:21,160 --> 00:05:22,640
We have captured them, Your Highness.

30
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,721
[Prince Nares]

31
00:05:25,477 --> 00:05:28,830
This one is a feisty fellow, and with quite the pair of spurs, too.

32
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,801
[Prince Ekathosarot]

33
00:05:47,623 --> 00:05:48,624
Catch it!

34
00:05:59,403 --> 00:06:03,320
Prince Nares, where are you?

35
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,760
Prince Nares!

36
00:06:06,917 --> 00:06:07,918
[Princess Suphankalaya]

37
00:06:08,750 --> 00:06:10,600
- Where are you?
- I'm here.

38
00:06:19,960 --> 00:06:21,120
Let the creature go.

39
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:23,641
Father has returned from Ayutthaya. He has summoned you.

40
00:06:23,710 --> 00:06:25,400
- He has summoned you.
- Father has returned.

41
00:06:36,537 --> 00:06:38,760
How is the situation in Ayutthaya?

42
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:40,100
[Queen Wisut Kasattri]

43
00:06:41,857 --> 00:06:44,100
His Majesty King Maha Chakkraphat has fallen ill.

44
00:06:44,110 --> 00:06:45,111
[Phra Maha Thammaracha, King of Phitsanulok]

45
00:06:45,157 --> 00:06:47,160
Thus, Prince Mahinthrathirat has been appointed to rule in his stead.

46
00:06:47,510 --> 00:06:50,040
With what ailment does His Majesty suffer, Your Majesty?

47
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:54,240
It is not serious.

48
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:57,281
The royal physicians say it was merely a fainting fit.

49
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:03,160
Ever since Ayutthaya fell

50
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,760
and became a vassal of Hongsawadi,

51
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,720
Father's heart has been consumed by grief.

52
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:16,320
The King surrendered so that the people might be spared from peril.

53
00:07:18,280 --> 00:07:20,281
His judgment was sound.

54
00:07:23,957 --> 00:07:26,640
- Father.
- Nares.

55
00:07:27,103 --> 00:07:29,040
Look at you. Be careful.

56
00:07:30,390 --> 00:07:32,040
My greetings, Your Highness.

57
00:07:34,477 --> 00:07:37,200
Come to me, my son

58
00:07:44,110 --> 00:07:45,111
Nares.

59
00:07:45,863 --> 00:07:48,200
And where are your siblings?

60
00:07:49,837 --> 00:07:51,800
Khao and I could not keep pace with him, Father.

61
00:07:51,897 --> 00:07:53,760
Dam ran as if he has wings

62
00:07:56,857 --> 00:07:59,520
Suphankalaya said that Father had summoned me.

63
00:08:00,170 --> 00:08:01,960
How could I afford to delay?

64
00:08:02,623 --> 00:08:05,760
When it comes to being headstrong, no one surpasses you.

65
00:08:06,463 --> 00:08:07,840
And look.

66
00:08:08,170 --> 00:08:11,480
Where were you playing? You’ve come back quite a mess.

67
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:18,440
You are covered in dirt from head to toe, my Khao.

68
00:08:19,310 --> 00:08:20,760
Let them play as they wish.

69
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:23,480
Soon, they will no longer have these moments together.

70
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:31,960
Your words carry a strange weight.

71
00:08:37,863 --> 00:08:40,240
King Bayinnaung has sent his royal command.

72
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:47,520
He demands that we send Prince Nares to reside in Hongsawadi.

73
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,600
He promises to provide for him as his own,

74
00:08:52,477 --> 00:08:54,760
to ensure a lasting peace between our two kingdoms.

75
00:09:00,097 --> 00:09:01,360
The three of you, leave us.

76
00:09:01,743 --> 00:09:04,160
I must speak with your father in private.

77
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:10,040
What madness is this? To take our son away as a hostage!

78
00:09:10,097 --> 00:09:11,120
It is not only our son.

79
00:09:12,277 --> 00:09:16,000
Every vassal state must offer their young princes and princesses

80
00:09:16,157 --> 00:09:17,158
to the Court of Hongsawadi.

81
00:09:17,877 --> 00:09:19,920
If others choose to surrender their children, so be it.

82
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:23,040
But my child shall stay with me!

83
00:09:23,783 --> 00:09:24,960
Be careful of your words.

84
00:09:30,490 --> 00:09:32,600
This is a royal mandate from King Bayinnaung.

85
00:09:34,610 --> 00:09:36,360
To defy him

86
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:39,640
is to be branded a rebel.

87
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:50,600
Living under their shadow...

88
00:09:53,137 --> 00:09:54,440
it is utterly suffocating.

89
00:09:59,303 --> 00:10:00,640
He is still so small.

90
00:10:02,030 --> 00:10:04,120
Not yet even nine years of age.

91
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,320
To be sent to a distant kingdom,

92
00:10:10,317 --> 00:10:11,760
What if they are cruel to him?

93
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:14,717
what could he possibly do?

94
00:10:14,923 --> 00:10:15,924
Mother.

95
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,001
Dam.

96
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,041
Mother.

97
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:26,920
Please don't cry.

98
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:29,960
If Father says I must go,

99
00:10:31,881 --> 00:10:33,040
then I shall go.

100
00:10:35,410 --> 00:10:36,520
I am not afraid.

101
00:10:39,457 --> 00:10:41,000
My prince.

102
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,321
[Hongsawadi 1564 A.D.]

103
00:11:01,137 --> 00:11:03,360
Your Majesty, I humbly crave your royal indulgence.

104
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:07,440
I beg your gracious permission to speak.

105
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:10,161
- [Binnya Dala, The Grand Minister]
- Bring forth the Princes and Princesses

106
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:12,280
of the vassal states:

107
00:11:12,557 --> 00:11:16,360
Hsenwi, Jinghong,

108
00:11:16,730 --> 00:11:19,240
Phetchabun, and Phitsanulok

109
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:23,200
to pay homage to His Majesty.

110
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:29,640
Princess Waen Kaew, daughter of Prince Hsenwi.

111
00:11:33,003 --> 00:11:37,240
Princess Noi Kham, daughter of Prince Jinghong.

112
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:40,320
Prince Mahawan,

113
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:44,160
son of the Lord of Phetchabun.

114
00:11:47,277 --> 00:11:48,378
Prince Nares,

115
00:11:48,983 --> 00:11:51,520
the Princes of Phitsanulok.

116
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:00,081
[Jaisingh, Phra Maha Uparaja]

117
00:12:00,181 --> 00:12:01,920
[The Royal Son of King Bayinnaung]

118
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:31,400
Prince from Phitsanulok.

119
00:12:31,497 --> 00:12:32,498
[King Bayinnaung]

120
00:12:32,880 --> 00:12:34,600
Why do you stare at me so?

121
00:12:36,362 --> 00:12:37,800
I seek to witness

122
00:12:39,080 --> 00:12:41,560
the might of the Conqueror of the Ten Directions.

123
00:12:43,363 --> 00:12:44,560
Now what is your judgment?

124
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:48,201
Your Majesty's stature is no different from any ordinary man.

125
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:52,360
How did you come to conquer the ten directions, Your Majesty?

126
00:12:56,401 --> 00:13:00,760
All men are born with two arms and two legs alike.

127
00:13:01,017 --> 00:13:03,080
But only those with superior wisdom

128
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:06,320
and greater diligence than all others

129
00:13:07,040 --> 00:13:09,240
can truly conquer the ten directions.

130
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:13,721
In that case, if I am equally diligent,

131
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:16,840
could I also conquer the ten directions?

132
00:13:20,721 --> 00:13:22,120
Is that not so, Your Majesty?

133
00:13:33,310 --> 00:13:34,800
He is but a child, yet so bold.

134
00:13:35,577 --> 00:13:37,640
Who has emboldened him to speak such words?

135
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:40,840
A sharp thorn needs no sharpening.

136
00:13:41,503 --> 00:13:44,960
Even with a teacher, a coward would never

137
00:13:46,143 --> 00:13:48,280
dare to speak such words.

138
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:51,363
A sharp thorn should be pruned while it is young.

139
00:13:51,550 --> 00:13:53,077
If left to grow,

140
00:13:53,183 --> 00:13:55,200
it will eventually turn and pierce us, Your Majesty.

141
00:13:57,640 --> 00:13:59,080
Why do you persist with such pestering?

142
00:14:00,290 --> 00:14:02,723
Is it your wish that I punish Prince Nares?

143
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:05,040
Only enough to teach him a lesson, Your Majesty.

144
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:07,720
King Maha Thammaracha of Phitsanulok

145
00:14:08,897 --> 00:14:10,400
is a formidable warrior.

146
00:14:11,583 --> 00:14:13,760
That we could conquer Ayutthaya this time

147
00:14:15,223 --> 00:14:17,161
is because Phitsanulok stands by our side.

148
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:19,280
To strike the son is to wound the father.

149
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:21,680
Should a few words from a child

150
00:14:22,663 --> 00:14:24,660
cause a rift between us and Phitsanulok?

151
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:26,880
Is that truly wise?

152
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:31,000
You aspire to be the King of Kings,

153
00:14:31,097 --> 00:14:32,720
the Supreme Emperor.

154
00:14:33,377 --> 00:14:35,920
You raised these princes,

155
00:14:36,197 --> 00:14:38,240
hoping for their future loyalty.

156
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:42,040
But this boy is insolent. He dares to speak as your equal.

157
00:14:42,423 --> 00:14:44,080
To not make an example of him

158
00:14:44,157 --> 00:14:45,530
would stain your honor, Your Majesty.

159
00:14:45,630 --> 00:14:46,760
Jaisingh.

160
00:14:48,337 --> 00:14:50,160
To be an Emperor of Emperors,

161
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:52,720
one must possess both might and mercy.

162
00:14:54,117 --> 00:14:56,360
One cannot rule by sheer force and punishment alone.

163
00:14:58,040 --> 00:15:01,160
If you seek to rule this kingdom after me,

164
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:03,040
remember this.

165
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:06,520
To defeat an enemy with the sword

166
00:15:08,040 --> 00:15:09,721
is nothing compared to winning their heart.

167
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:20,680
[Lord Sapphaphet Phakdi, The Royal Mentor]

168
00:15:25,303 --> 00:15:26,960
Are you sure you want to keep it here, Your Highness?

169
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:29,960
Lueang must feel out of place here too.

170
00:15:31,443 --> 00:15:34,720
Let him stay here for tonight.

171
00:15:34,983 --> 00:15:37,240
Tomorrow, we shall find a better way.

172
00:15:37,537 --> 00:15:38,538
Yes, Your Highness.

173
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,560
Fear not, Lueang.

174
00:15:53,070 --> 00:15:55,320
I will not keep you locked in a cage.

175
00:15:57,720 --> 00:15:58,760
Tomorrow,

176
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:02,760
Khun Phranai shall find you a better home.

177
00:16:06,560 --> 00:16:08,600
But you must remain on your guard.

178
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:12,921
For this place

179
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:17,040
is vast and grand,

180
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:22,160
yet it is not our home.

181
00:16:47,523 --> 00:16:49,600
Look, the captives.

182
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:52,640
[Minye Kyawswa]

183
00:16:53,297 --> 00:16:54,298
This way, Your Highness.

184
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:08,280
Come here, captive.

185
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:14,840
You too.

186
00:17:17,897 --> 00:17:19,200
I am no captive.

187
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:22,040
How are you not?

188
00:17:22,637 --> 00:17:25,640
- My father said you are a captive.
- I am not.

189
00:17:25,880 --> 00:17:27,160
- You are.
- I am not.

190
00:17:27,283 --> 00:17:29,880
I said you're a captive, so you are one!

191
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:33,920
- Your Highness, please do not!
- Let go!

192
00:17:36,517 --> 00:17:38,120
Teach him a lesson for me.

193
00:17:40,123 --> 00:17:42,000
Let me go! Let me go!

194
00:17:42,263 --> 00:17:43,601
- Let go!
- Stop it!

195
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:46,880
[Mingyi Swa]

196
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:53,600
Brawling within the Royal Grounds,

197
00:17:53,960 --> 00:17:56,080
do you not know the gravity of such an offense?

198
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:58,840
This captive slave tried to strike me.

199
00:18:01,117 --> 00:18:02,520
He hurt me first.

200
00:18:03,397 --> 00:18:04,463
Who are you?

201
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:06,550
My name is Nares.

202
00:18:07,183 --> 00:18:10,561
I am the son of King Maha Thammaracha, the Sovereign of Phitsanulok.

203
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:13,957
I am Mingyi Swa.

204
00:18:14,250 --> 00:18:17,480
Son of the Crown Prince Jaisingh.

205
00:18:17,723 --> 00:18:20,724
Grandson of the Great King Bayinnaung of Hongsawadi,

206
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:24,400
and the elder brother of this foul-mouthed boy.

207
00:18:26,950 --> 00:18:28,240
Minye Kyawswa

208
00:18:28,597 --> 00:18:30,803
If I inform Grandfather

209
00:18:31,123 --> 00:18:32,560
that you have harmed Prince Nares,

210
00:18:32,978 --> 00:18:34,297
you will face a severe punishment.

211
00:18:34,477 --> 00:18:35,480
All of you will.

212
00:18:37,530 --> 00:18:40,560
This time, I apologize on my brother’s behalf.

213
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:43,281
Can we simply let this matter rest?

214
00:18:46,517 --> 00:18:47,518
Very well.

215
00:18:48,518 --> 00:18:51,560
You are not yet of age for lessons. Go play elsewhere.

216
00:18:53,203 --> 00:18:54,280
I said, leave!

217
00:19:02,560 --> 00:19:03,840
The Royal Tutor has arrived, Your Highness.

218
00:19:15,057 --> 00:19:16,058
Nares.

219
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:46,920
How is my boy?

220
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:49,720
Lord Sapphaphet has informed us

221
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,440
that Prince Nares is well and in good spirits.

222
00:19:53,600 --> 00:19:56,000
King Bayinnaung has granted him a residence

223
00:19:56,483 --> 00:19:58,560
equal to those of the Princes of Hongsawadi.

224
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:01,881
That is a relief.

225
00:20:03,760 --> 00:20:04,840
And what else, You Majesty?

226
00:20:07,503 --> 00:20:10,320
He is taught to read, write, and study semantics.

227
00:20:10,703 --> 00:20:13,440
He masters the Treatises of War and the use of all weapons.

228
00:20:15,397 --> 00:20:18,200
Prince Nares is brillian and learns with great speed.

229
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:23,800
King Bayinnaung holds our son in the highest favor.

230
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:39,440
[Mingyi Swa]

231
00:20:43,840 --> 00:20:45,250
[Prince Nares]

232
00:20:53,737 --> 00:20:55,840
Prince Nares has a true warrior's skill.

233
00:20:56,760 --> 00:20:58,600
Truly, he is his father's son.

234
00:21:02,717 --> 00:21:04,440
And what about Mingyi Swa?

235
00:21:05,280 --> 00:21:06,641
Your son is not like you.

236
00:21:07,881 --> 00:21:12,000
In battle, he is no match for Prince Nares.

237
00:21:15,670 --> 00:21:17,720
I shall discipline my son more strictly, Your Majesty.

238
00:21:19,390 --> 00:21:21,600
No two men are born alike.

239
00:21:25,023 --> 00:21:28,720
Prince Nares is brilliant, swift,

240
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:31,360
and sharp in combat.

241
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:33,561
He is destined to be a Great General.

242
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:37,120
As for my grandson, Mingyi Swa,

243
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,720
he is wise, calm,

244
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:43,680
and broad-minded.

245
00:21:44,750 --> 00:21:46,360
He is destined to be a Sovereign.

246
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,240
A reward for the victor.

247
00:22:05,523 --> 00:22:06,880
You are most gracious, Your Majesty.

248
00:22:13,840 --> 00:22:15,880
And what of the reward for the loser, Your Majesty?

249
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:19,840
You have lost. Why should you receive a reward?

250
00:22:21,197 --> 00:22:22,440
Where there is darkness, there is light.

251
00:22:22,797 --> 00:22:24,400
Where there is night, there is day.

252
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:27,840
Without the defeated, how could there be a victor, Your Majesty?

253
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:29,881
Thus,

254
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:33,640
the defeated are as vital as the triumphant.

255
00:22:34,120 --> 00:22:35,880
You have a sharp tongue indeed, my grandson.

256
00:22:37,170 --> 00:22:38,171
Here, take it.

257
00:22:50,090 --> 00:22:51,091
Mingyi Swa.

258
00:22:52,963 --> 00:22:54,680
Change your way of thinking.

259
00:22:55,477 --> 00:22:56,520
On the battlefield,

260
00:22:57,120 --> 00:22:59,480
the defeated are as good as the dead.

261
00:23:00,243 --> 00:23:02,720
And the dead possess no importance whatsoever.

262
00:23:05,403 --> 00:23:06,760
Yes, Your Highness.

263
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:32,360
Hurry, Brother! I must show you something special.

264
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:53,120
[Kuy Village]

265
00:24:21,090 --> 00:24:22,091
Doctor Suk!

266
00:24:25,663 --> 00:24:26,930
Are you inside?

267
00:24:27,130 --> 00:24:30,800
Who is that? Why all this noise?

268
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:32,001
[Muy]

269
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:34,360
Hah! This brat.

270
00:24:42,760 --> 00:24:43,761
[Master Suk]

271
00:24:43,997 --> 00:24:45,950
Your Highness.

272
00:24:47,217 --> 00:24:49,520
Mind your tongue! He is a Prince.

273
00:24:49,697 --> 00:24:51,880
Careful, or your head will roll from your shoulders!

274
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:53,440
Execution is too swift for her.

275
00:24:53,543 --> 00:24:55,280
I shall lash her to a post instead.

276
00:24:55,300 --> 00:24:57,480
And force her to feast on elephant dung instead of rice for a full month!

277
00:24:58,437 --> 00:24:59,438
Your Highness.

278
00:24:59,863 --> 00:25:02,720
Your Highness, I beg for your mercy on behalf of my daughter.

279
00:25:04,923 --> 00:25:08,400
She was raised in the wild, among the thickets.

280
00:25:10,820 --> 00:25:12,440
I was merely jesting.

281
00:25:12,770 --> 00:25:14,560
I see her as my own sister.

282
00:25:17,837 --> 00:25:21,120
But tell me, how fares my Muang?

283
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:23,400
Muang.

284
00:25:26,863 --> 00:25:29,040
There are countless elephants in the Royal Stables.

285
00:25:29,877 --> 00:25:31,360
Why come all this way to see it?

286
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:34,960
Those are the King's elephants. But this one is mine.

287
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:42,200
Muang went out for some fun

288
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,440
and stepped on a spike.

289
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:46,320
I have applied the herbal poultice.

290
00:25:46,477 --> 00:25:48,120
He will recover in a few days.

291
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:56,720
Is this what we traversed all this way to find?

292
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:01,360
Not quite. The real treasure is yet to come. Just wait.

293
00:26:02,360 --> 00:26:03,600
I am here, Your Highness.

294
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:13,760
The 'Fifth Month Mead,' brewed by my own hands.

295
00:26:13,923 --> 00:26:16,000
I offer it to you as an apology for my insolence.

296
00:26:25,383 --> 00:26:26,384
Ah.

297
00:26:43,623 --> 00:26:44,640
This is a fine brew indeed.

298
00:26:46,520 --> 00:26:49,880
Believe me, Muy has many more jars hidden away.

299
00:26:50,203 --> 00:26:52,600
Next time, we shall raid her stash once more.

300
00:26:54,704 --> 00:26:55,760
Enough.

301
00:26:56,523 --> 00:27:00,040
Should my father learn that I have slipped away to play like this,

302
00:27:00,840 --> 00:27:02,120
it would mean grave trouble for us both.

303
00:27:03,560 --> 00:27:04,720
What is it that you fear?

304
00:27:05,030 --> 00:27:08,480
Phra Maha Uparaja, whom they say is so fearsome,

305
00:27:08,697 --> 00:27:12,080
has never dared to lay a finger on you.

306
00:27:20,390 --> 00:27:21,560
My father loves me dearly.

307
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:24,281
But alas…

308
00:27:26,623 --> 00:27:28,000
Had I but half your talent,

309
00:27:28,740 --> 00:27:30,280
my father would be truly proud.

310
00:27:33,023 --> 00:27:36,000
You are capable, Brother, but it is not enough.

311
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:38,880
Your father wishes for you to surpass all others.

312
00:27:39,280 --> 00:27:40,440
For in the days to come,

313
00:27:41,120 --> 00:27:42,721
you must rule over men.

314
00:27:46,521 --> 00:27:48,522
But I shall not rule my people with the sword.

315
00:27:56,170 --> 00:27:59,560
Others will still use the sword against you.

316
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:01,241
How will you respond?

317
00:28:11,777 --> 00:28:13,100
Why then should I fear?

318
00:28:14,280 --> 00:28:17,720
With you by my side, I shall simply leave the fighting to you.

319
00:28:23,583 --> 00:28:25,880
And this is your payment in advance.

320
00:28:28,077 --> 00:28:29,078
Payment?

321
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:37,281
[Ayutthaya, 1568 A.D.]

322
00:28:47,063 --> 00:28:48,880
Is it truly as you say, Phraya Ram?

323
00:28:50,383 --> 00:28:51,720
- [King Mahinthrathirat, King of Ayutthaya]
- Indeed it is, Your Majesty.

324
00:28:54,610 --> 00:28:56,280
Presenting His Highness, King Maha Thammaracha!

325
00:29:09,630 --> 00:29:11,560
King Mahinthrathirat.

326
00:29:15,883 --> 00:29:18,320
We are both Sovereigns of tributary kingdoms,

327
00:29:18,810 --> 00:29:20,240
equal in rank.

328
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:23,000
Furthermore, I am your elder.

329
00:29:24,070 --> 00:29:25,401
Now that I have come to visit,

330
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:28,480
why do you show no respect?

331
00:29:28,943 --> 00:29:30,920
And why have you not prepared a seat befitting my station?

332
00:29:31,630 --> 00:29:33,840
A man knows his own deeds in the depths of his heart.

333
00:29:34,897 --> 00:29:37,250
You turned traitor, aiding Hongsawadi,

334
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:39,520
leading their armies to crush and conquer Ayutthaya.

335
00:29:39,930 --> 00:29:41,800
Do you still expect me to call you kinsman?

336
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:45,360
Had Ayutthaya not forsaken us first

337
00:29:45,957 --> 00:29:47,730
Never would Phitsanulok have been forced.

338
00:29:47,783 --> 00:29:49,731
You rule Phitsanulok only because

339
00:29:50,430 --> 00:29:53,031
my father bestowed that honor upon you!

340
00:29:53,790 --> 00:29:55,840
Instead of laying down your life to repay his grace,

341
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:59,440
You saved your own skin by hiding behind our enemies!

342
00:30:00,397 --> 00:30:01,480
Is it because

343
00:30:01,837 --> 00:30:05,080
Bayinnaug now shields your wretched head,

344
00:30:05,603 --> 00:30:07,880
that you dare come here and flaunt your power in my face?

345
00:30:10,750 --> 00:30:13,880
Enough! My presence here

346
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:16,960
is not to trade words with a fool.

347
00:30:20,503 --> 00:30:21,480
Phraya Ram.

348
00:30:21,504 --> 00:30:22,505
[Phraya Ram, Lord of Chanthabun]

349
00:30:23,043 --> 00:30:25,400
- My Lord?
- You hold the title of Lord of Chanthabun,

350
00:30:25,590 --> 00:30:27,560
yet you linger here in the capital.

351
00:30:27,797 --> 00:30:31,000
- This is highly improper.
- I require Phraya Ram’s service here, by my side.

352
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:34,120
Leaving him here will only breed discord and lead Your Majesty astray.

353
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:38,000
The position of Lord of Phichai is now vacant.

354
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:40,720
I ask that Your Majesty

355
00:30:41,337 --> 00:30:44,040
appoint Phraya Ram as Lord of Phichai,

356
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:45,680
to assist me

357
00:30:45,917 --> 00:30:48,400
- in governing the Northern Provinces.
- How dare you!

358
00:30:48,418 --> 00:30:49,480
This is the Royal Command

359
00:30:50,517 --> 00:30:52,160
of Bayinnaung,

360
00:30:53,757 --> 00:30:54,880
King of Hongsawadi!

361
00:31:08,217 --> 00:31:10,218
[Border Forest, outside the City of Ayutthaya]

362
00:31:42,230 --> 00:31:43,231
Watch out!

363
00:32:15,103 --> 00:32:16,104
Poison.

364
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:39,281
[Chan Royal Palace, Phitsanulok - 1568 A.D.]

365
00:32:47,043 --> 00:32:49,650
Go and summon Princess Suphankalaya and Prince Ekathosarot

366
00:32:49,770 --> 00:32:50,920
to my presence at once.

367
00:32:58,840 --> 00:33:00,841
[Princess Suphankalaya]

368
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:11,401
[Prince Ekathosarot]

369
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:16,280
King Mahinthrathirat has sent a royal letter informing us

370
00:33:16,590 --> 00:33:18,520
that your grandfather is gravely ill.

371
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:20,240
His condition is worsening.

372
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:23,640
And he has commanded that I bring you both to his bedside.

373
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:25,760
When shall you be leaving, Mother?

374
00:33:29,920 --> 00:33:32,840
Ayutthaya has dispatched a Royal Envoy with five hundred men.

375
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:34,750
along with a fleet of Royal Barges.

376
00:33:34,977 --> 00:33:37,960
Both the men and the vessels have now arrived.

377
00:33:38,760 --> 00:33:41,800
How could our Royal Uncle expect us all to abandon the city like this?

378
00:33:42,800 --> 00:33:46,240
Father has not yet returned. Will you not wait for him first?

379
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:49,840
But if your grandfather is truly in grave danger,

380
00:33:50,497 --> 00:33:51,880
And I should delay,

381
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:55,040
then I would be a daughter most unfilial.

382
00:33:58,880 --> 00:34:00,360
What should I do?

383
00:34:11,063 --> 00:34:13,600
A royal letter from Princess Suphankalaya, Your Highness.

384
00:34:30,560 --> 00:34:31,561
Prince Nares.

385
00:34:33,443 --> 00:34:34,445
Prince Nares.

386
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:39,720
Wait. Where are you going in such haste?

387
00:34:40,241 --> 00:34:41,960
I have urgent matters to attend to.

388
00:34:45,670 --> 00:34:46,671
Do not follow me.

389
00:34:57,297 --> 00:34:59,583
Well? Say it.

390
00:34:59,957 --> 00:35:01,440
What is so pressing

391
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:04,080
that you must disturb me at such an early hour?

392
00:35:05,680 --> 00:35:09,200
I humbly crave Your Majesty’s leave to return to Phitsanulok.

393
00:35:10,703 --> 00:35:11,704
For what reason?

394
00:35:12,450 --> 00:35:15,040
My mother and my siblings were lured to Ayutthaya

395
00:35:15,103 --> 00:35:16,240
and are now being held as captives.

396
00:35:16,537 --> 00:35:18,400
My father went to negotiate with King Mahinthrathirat,

397
00:35:18,590 --> 00:35:21,280
But he has not yet returned, and his whereabouts remain unknown.

398
00:35:29,797 --> 00:35:32,720
From where did you hear such news?

399
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:37,200
The letter from Princess Suphankalaya arrived this very day, Your Highness.

400
00:35:40,297 --> 00:35:42,200
King Mahinthrathirat bears a deep-seated grudge

401
00:35:42,360 --> 00:35:44,880
for Phitsanulok's shift of loyalty to Hongsawadi.

402
00:35:45,240 --> 00:35:46,840
Now, he may seize this chance to take his revenge.

403
00:35:48,563 --> 00:35:52,120
Phitsanulok is now a vassal of Hongsawadi.

404
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:55,441
Yet King Mahinthrathirat dares to detain the consort

405
00:35:56,310 --> 00:35:58,360
and the sons of its Lord.

406
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:00,480
This is a grave insolence.

407
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:03,917
It challenges my very authority. It shall not be tolerated.

408
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:06,840
- Jaisingh.
- Your Majesty.

409
00:36:07,760 --> 00:36:11,841
Let Binnya Dala dispatch royal seals to all vassal lords.

410
00:36:12,120 --> 00:36:13,163
Command them to seek an audience with me at once.

411
00:36:13,721 --> 00:36:16,100
Prepare all troops and provisions.

412
00:36:16,563 --> 00:36:18,950
For we shall march our armies to Ayutthaya.

413
00:36:19,997 --> 00:36:21,600
As you command, Your Majesty.

414
00:36:38,663 --> 00:36:40,160
Your Majesty.

415
00:36:41,164 --> 00:36:42,200
What is it now?

416
00:36:44,130 --> 00:36:46,480
I beg your permission to join this campaign, Your Majesty.

417
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:51,400
So, you wish to go to war?

418
00:36:52,203 --> 00:36:54,080
I wish to save my mother and my siblings, Your Majesty.

419
00:36:57,223 --> 00:36:59,960
Very well. You are of age now.

420
00:37:00,903 --> 00:37:04,280
Prove your mettle in battle, so that all may fear and respect you.

421
00:37:04,960 --> 00:37:07,161
I shall appoint you as a Commander.

422
00:37:07,800 --> 00:37:11,440
Lead a hundred men and join the vanguard in this conquest.

423
00:37:13,063 --> 00:37:14,364
Your mercy is boundless, Your Majesty.

424
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:19,165
In that case, I beg Your Majesty's to let my son join the vanguard.

425
00:37:20,800 --> 00:37:22,160
When I was your age,

426
00:37:22,817 --> 00:37:25,080
I fought shoulder to shoulder with your grandfather.

427
00:37:25,923 --> 00:37:28,560
What say you, Mingyi Swa?

428
00:37:37,723 --> 00:37:39,800
In all honesty,

429
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:42,001
I have no desire for war.

430
00:37:43,240 --> 00:37:44,241
But…

431
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:49,960
I wish to my help ounger brother, Your Majesty.

432
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:04,520
I hereby appoint the Crown Prince as our vanguard.

433
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:06,240
You shall command twenty thousand troops

434
00:38:06,560 --> 00:38:07,840
and lead the march ahead of the main host.

435
00:38:08,800 --> 00:38:09,801
Yes, Your Majesty.

436
00:38:10,040 --> 00:38:13,360
I, myself, shall command the main host and follow thereafter.

437
00:38:13,950 --> 00:38:16,400
The Kings of Inwa and Prome,

438
00:38:16,990 --> 00:38:19,800
Lord Binnya Dala, Lord Saen Luang,

439
00:38:20,083 --> 00:38:21,084
and Lord Pathein,

440
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:25,040
each shall lead their own provincial forces,

441
00:38:25,950 --> 00:38:28,320
and unite our strength as we march forward together.

442
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:31,400
By your command, Your Majesty.

443
00:38:32,263 --> 00:38:35,680
For this campaign, I hereby appoint

444
00:38:36,217 --> 00:38:38,480
Mingyi Swa and Prince Nares

445
00:38:39,240 --> 00:38:42,640
as commanders of a hundred-man unit

446
00:38:43,070 --> 00:38:44,800
to join our forces in this conquest.

447
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:56,241
[City of Ayutthaya]

448
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:00,641
Move!

449
00:39:03,430 --> 00:39:05,642
Since you refuse to let me pass,

450
00:39:06,122 --> 00:39:08,840
then go and summon your Sovereign!

451
00:39:09,320 --> 00:39:11,280
- Tell him to come and speak with me here.
- I am already here.

452
00:39:14,957 --> 00:39:18,720
My sister is a Supreme Consort,

453
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:21,850
the glory of both Phitsanulok and Ayutthaya.

454
00:39:22,603 --> 00:39:25,920
Why then do you behave like a common woman in the marketplace?

455
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:30,800
Since you remember well who I am,

456
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:32,760
how then do you dare to imprison me?

457
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:35,800
You hold me and my sons as hostages

458
00:39:35,930 --> 00:39:38,120
to force King Maha Thammaracha into submission.

459
00:39:39,003 --> 00:39:42,840
Does our blood mean nothing to you now?

460
00:39:44,710 --> 00:39:45,711
Originally,

461
00:39:46,111 --> 00:39:49,280
Phitsanulok and Ayutthaya shared no bond.

462
00:39:50,463 --> 00:39:52,840
It was only through your marriage, Sister,

463
00:39:53,840 --> 00:39:56,160
that I forced myself to call them kin.

464
00:39:57,797 --> 00:40:00,280
But once King Maha Thammaracha is gone,

465
00:40:01,417 --> 00:40:03,720
this fragile bond shall be severed forever.

466
00:40:05,703 --> 00:40:06,704
You…

467
00:40:07,297 --> 00:40:09,880
Do you truly intend to kill your own brother-in-law?

468
00:40:11,960 --> 00:40:15,280
I shall reclaim Phitsanulok from the grip of Hongsawadi.

469
00:40:16,903 --> 00:40:20,200
Should King Maha Thammaracha refuse to submit,

470
00:40:20,640 --> 00:40:22,160
then he shall learn the cost of his defiance.

471
00:40:26,030 --> 00:40:27,031
Guards!

472
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:31,601
Escort Her Highness Queen Wisut Kasattri to the inner chambers.

473
00:40:32,543 --> 00:40:34,520
And see to it that she never steps foot outside again.

474
00:40:35,843 --> 00:40:37,560
Should my sister prove disobedient,

475
00:40:38,583 --> 00:40:40,800
You have my leave to punish her as you see fit.

476
00:40:42,200 --> 00:40:43,720
Yes, Your Majesty.

477
00:40:51,440 --> 00:40:53,700
[12th month , Year 1568 ]

478
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:20,701
[ Military Camp, Kamphaeng Phet]

479
00:41:42,930 --> 00:41:45,680
Watch your step, Commander Mingyi Swa.

480
00:41:48,297 --> 00:41:51,320
Come then, Nares! I do not fear you.

481
00:42:14,263 --> 00:42:15,960
Brother, Brother.

482
00:42:18,303 --> 00:42:20,160
It is nothing. I merely slipped.

483
00:42:28,480 --> 00:42:29,880
I thought I had struck you, Brother.

484
00:42:44,403 --> 00:42:45,640
This blade is incredibly keen.

485
00:42:46,597 --> 00:42:48,360
Far sharper than the practice swords we’ve used.

486
00:42:50,410 --> 00:42:53,800
Had you not stayed your hand just now, it would have surely tasted my blood.

487
00:42:55,360 --> 00:42:58,640
Fear not, Brother. For my blade

488
00:42:58,970 --> 00:43:00,600
shall taste only the blood of my enemies.

489
00:43:09,997 --> 00:43:10,998
That.

490
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:20,680
This fabric looks expensive.

491
00:43:22,200 --> 00:43:23,320
It does not belongs to commoners.

492
00:43:26,477 --> 00:43:27,560
Not our own men either.

493
00:43:29,797 --> 00:43:30,798
Then to whom does it belong?

494
00:43:38,440 --> 00:43:39,657
Brother, return to the camp at once.

495
00:43:39,957 --> 00:43:41,160
Tell our men to stay alert and be ready.

496
00:43:42,363 --> 00:43:43,364
Nares.

497
00:43:44,390 --> 00:43:45,391
Nares.

498
00:43:56,483 --> 00:43:57,484
Smoke.

499
00:45:07,997 --> 00:45:08,998
Father.

500
00:45:26,743 --> 00:45:28,720
I did not expect to find you here.

501
00:45:31,200 --> 00:45:33,920
What has happened? Why are you here, Father?

502
00:45:35,280 --> 00:45:36,760
I have fled from Ayutthaya.

503
00:45:37,397 --> 00:45:39,200
Mahinthrathirat sent men to assassinate me.

504
00:45:41,043 --> 00:45:44,120
They used poisoned arrows, but I survived.

505
00:45:45,083 --> 00:45:46,840
I began my journey only after my wounds had healed.

506
00:45:48,323 --> 00:45:50,100
I have only just arrived in Kamphaeng Phet this very day.

507
00:45:52,200 --> 00:45:56,040
So that is why. Uncle knew his assassins had failed.

508
00:45:56,683 --> 00:45:58,184
He feared your vengeance.

509
00:45:59,197 --> 00:46:01,080
So he took Mother and Khao as hostages.

510
00:46:02,583 --> 00:46:03,584
What did you say?

511
00:46:04,163 --> 00:46:07,290
Mother and my brother are in Ayutthaya. I am going to save them.

512
00:46:13,164 --> 00:46:15,240
I crave your royal permission, Your Majesty.

513
00:46:17,000 --> 00:46:20,040
- What is it?
- We have captured another one, Your Majesty.

514
00:46:22,870 --> 00:46:24,960
- Let me go!
- Walk!

515
00:46:25,363 --> 00:46:26,364
Let go of me!

516
00:46:32,157 --> 00:46:33,650
- Brother.
- Nares.

517
00:46:35,363 --> 00:46:36,364
Let go of him.

518
00:46:40,897 --> 00:46:43,760
I told you to wait at the camp, why did you follow me?

519
00:46:45,520 --> 00:46:48,240
You were gone for so long. I was worried, so I followed you.

520
00:46:55,583 --> 00:46:56,640
This is Mingyi Swa.

521
00:46:57,143 --> 00:46:59,520
The son of Crown Prince Jaisingh, Father.

522
00:47:04,160 --> 00:47:07,120
The King of Hongsawadi has commanded us to march upon Ayutthaya.

523
00:47:07,777 --> 00:47:09,240
We are going to bring Mother home.

524
00:47:29,430 --> 00:47:32,040
I am truly gladdened that you are safe.

525
00:47:32,840 --> 00:47:33,841
Please, do take a seat.

526
00:47:35,400 --> 00:47:36,842
You are most gracious, Your Majesty.

527
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:48,280
My suspicions were correct.

528
00:47:49,210 --> 00:47:51,760
King Mahinthrathirat seized the chance to assassinate you.

529
00:47:54,023 --> 00:47:55,680
We must teach them a lesson they will never forget.

530
00:47:57,920 --> 00:47:59,120
King Maha Thammaracha,

531
00:48:00,520 --> 00:48:02,320
your arrival here is most opportune.

532
00:48:03,320 --> 00:48:05,760
Mobilize your forces from Phitsanulok

533
00:48:05,977 --> 00:48:08,880
to join with the army of Crown Prince Jaisingh

534
00:48:09,617 --> 00:48:12,300
and strike Ayutthaya from the eastern front.

535
00:48:14,657 --> 00:48:15,720
Yes, Your Majesty.

536
00:48:16,240 --> 00:48:17,920
Mingyi Swa and Nares,

537
00:48:18,720 --> 00:48:20,320
go and reinforce the vanguard at once.

538
00:48:21,120 --> 00:48:22,320
As for the other divisions,

539
00:48:22,517 --> 00:48:24,560
encircle the city from all four directions.

540
00:48:25,800 --> 00:48:27,960
Conquer Ayutthaya at any cost.

541
00:48:28,350 --> 00:48:29,351
Yes, Your Majesty.

542
00:52:31,410 --> 00:52:35,440
Your Majesty, King Bayinnaung leads the grand army himself this time.

543
00:52:36,157 --> 00:52:38,600
Supported by legions from all major provinces,

544
00:52:39,163 --> 00:52:40,840
they have us surrounded on every side.

545
00:52:41,757 --> 00:52:45,160
Our terrain remains strong. We can still hold our ground.

546
00:52:45,443 --> 00:52:46,445
However…

547
00:52:47,010 --> 00:52:48,011
What is it?

548
00:52:48,203 --> 00:52:50,330
The vanguard, led by King Maha Thammaracha

549
00:52:50,523 --> 00:52:54,360
and the Crown Prince of Hongsawadi,

550
00:52:54,930 --> 00:52:57,880
is closing in on our city walls, Your Majesty!

551
00:52:58,000 --> 00:53:00,640
Then hold them back, damn it!

552
00:53:01,040 --> 00:53:04,480
But King Maha Thammaracha and Prince Nares

553
00:53:04,880 --> 00:53:07,520
take turns leading the charge, day and night, without rest.

554
00:53:08,120 --> 00:53:10,121
Their only goal is to reclaim the hostages at any cost.

555
00:53:11,263 --> 00:53:14,920
I believe we should return Her Majesty

556
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:17,680
and Prince Ekathosarot to them.

557
00:53:18,403 --> 00:53:19,840
Once their fury is appeased,

558
00:53:20,480 --> 00:53:22,680
we may then negotiate for peace.

559
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:28,200
Your Majesty, if those two reach our walls,

560
00:53:28,400 --> 00:53:30,401
we will not be able to hold them back!

561
00:53:42,737 --> 00:53:44,280
Mother, Mother.

562
00:53:56,923 --> 00:53:57,924
Mother.

563
00:53:58,757 --> 00:54:00,063
Father and Nares have prevailed.

564
00:54:00,777 --> 00:54:02,212
They have reached the city walls, Mother.

565
00:54:05,930 --> 00:54:06,960
Why is that, Mother?

566
00:54:08,430 --> 00:54:09,800
Aren't you happy?

567
00:54:15,840 --> 00:54:17,560
I know not what to feel.

568
00:54:24,263 --> 00:54:25,920
On one side is my brother.

569
00:54:28,520 --> 00:54:31,360
On the other, my husband and son.

570
00:54:34,110 --> 00:54:35,360
Ayutthaya

571
00:54:37,230 --> 00:54:39,160
is my birthplace,

572
00:54:43,240 --> 00:54:46,640
yet Phitsanulok is where I shall rest forever.

573
00:54:51,090 --> 00:54:53,480
Victory or defeat,

574
00:54:58,560 --> 00:55:00,040
for me there is no joy to be found.

575
00:55:02,437 --> 00:55:05,880
And if Ayutthaya falls,

576
00:55:07,290 --> 00:55:08,680
What will happen to us, Mother?

577
00:55:10,440 --> 00:55:13,000
King Bayinnaung will execute your uncle,

578
00:55:14,950 --> 00:55:16,510
and appoint someone else

579
00:55:17,870 --> 00:55:19,920
to rule over Ayutthaya.

580
00:55:26,777 --> 00:55:28,320
And what if Ayutthaya wins?

581
00:55:33,343 --> 00:55:35,720
Hongsawadi would withdraw its forces,

582
00:55:37,920 --> 00:55:40,040
leaving Phitsanulok

583
00:55:41,670 --> 00:55:43,760
under Ayutthaya's rule once more.

584
00:55:49,010 --> 00:55:50,041
But you…

585
00:55:53,880 --> 00:55:55,181
you would lose

586
00:55:57,670 --> 00:55:59,143
both your father

587
00:56:00,390 --> 00:56:01,663
and your brother.

588
00:56:04,120 --> 00:56:05,521
For they would both fight

589
00:56:07,397 --> 00:56:08,800
until their very last breath.

590
00:56:17,037 --> 00:56:18,240
Then, for all the prayers you offer,

591
00:56:20,110 --> 00:56:21,640
for whom do you ask for a blessing, Mother?

592
00:56:26,950 --> 00:56:28,160
I pray

593
00:56:28,737 --> 00:56:31,640
for the protection of this land.

594
00:56:33,520 --> 00:56:36,160
Whichever hands are destined to save this kingdom,

595
00:56:38,717 --> 00:56:40,560
may the heavens

596
00:56:43,503 --> 00:56:45,120
grant them victory.

597
00:57:21,290 --> 00:57:24,040
Wait, Prince Nares! It is I, Phraya Ram.

598
00:57:24,063 --> 00:57:25,280
Do you remember me?

599
00:57:39,457 --> 00:57:42,250
I once attended your court at Chan Palace, when you were a child.

600
00:57:44,400 --> 00:57:46,920
- We have it, Your Highness.
- Wow.

601
00:57:47,177 --> 00:57:49,400
It is so big.

602
00:57:50,990 --> 00:57:54,017
This one is a feisty fellow, and with quite the pair of spurs, too.

603
00:58:01,410 --> 00:58:02,411
Phraya Ram.

604
00:58:06,290 --> 00:58:08,840
My loyalty to King Maha Thammaracha has never wavered.

605
00:58:09,803 --> 00:58:12,360
In the chaos, I failed to recognize Your Highness.

606
00:58:12,700 --> 00:58:14,120
Please forgive me.

607
00:58:22,477 --> 00:58:23,478
Nares!

608
00:58:41,443 --> 00:58:42,550
Nares!

609
00:59:37,583 --> 00:59:38,584
Nares!

610
00:59:41,397 --> 00:59:42,398
Nares!

611
01:00:50,210 --> 01:00:51,440
My master taught us.

612
01:00:53,637 --> 01:00:55,200
When facing an enemy,

613
01:00:55,840 --> 01:00:57,960
be steadfast, and never waver.

614
01:01:01,040 --> 01:01:02,841
You were about to take his life.

615
01:01:03,870 --> 01:01:05,320
Why did you stay your hand?

616
01:01:10,230 --> 01:01:11,640
I knew him once.

617
01:01:13,557 --> 01:01:14,920
When I was but a boy,

618
01:01:16,030 --> 01:01:17,960
Phraya Ram was very kind to me.

619
01:01:23,440 --> 01:01:25,560
But now, you both stand on opposite sides.

620
01:01:27,017 --> 01:01:28,440
He is your enemy.

621
01:01:32,023 --> 01:01:33,024
In the past,

622
01:01:34,877 --> 01:01:36,440
I believed that war

623
01:01:37,043 --> 01:01:39,080
was simply about killing strangers

624
01:01:40,163 --> 01:01:41,920
or those not of our kind.

625
01:01:45,723 --> 01:01:49,160
But in the reality of battle, be it a friend,

626
01:01:49,737 --> 01:01:50,738
a brother,

627
01:01:51,223 --> 01:01:53,200
or someone you once knew so well,

628
01:01:54,750 --> 01:01:57,960
if they stand on the opposite side, you must be prepared to kill them.

629
01:01:59,640 --> 01:02:00,641
Nares.

630
01:02:02,320 --> 01:02:03,920
We grew up together.

631
01:02:06,600 --> 01:02:09,120
I loved you like my own brother.

632
01:02:12,120 --> 01:02:15,560
I, too, saw you as my own elder brother.

633
01:02:18,560 --> 01:02:19,561
We both

634
01:02:20,870 --> 01:02:23,040
were meant to stay on the same side forever.

635
01:02:23,920 --> 01:02:24,921
Was that not the promise?

636
01:02:26,800 --> 01:02:28,400
If you stand by my side,

637
01:02:29,757 --> 01:02:31,280
I shall stand by yours.

638
01:02:34,117 --> 01:02:35,800
This is my solemn oath.

639
01:02:49,090 --> 01:02:50,720
This is my solemn oath.

640
01:03:19,837 --> 01:03:21,640
We ask for Princess Suphankalaya

641
01:03:21,870 --> 01:03:23,720
to be my royal consort.

642
01:03:23,871 --> 01:03:26,080
The matter of Princess Suphankalaya is no concern of yours.

643
01:03:26,100 --> 01:03:28,920
Prince Nares is my brother. His sorrow is my own.

644
01:03:29,067 --> 01:03:33,470
Both of you being close to King Bayinnaung could prove to be an advantage.

645
01:03:33,500 --> 01:03:35,001
What is your true intent?

646
01:03:35,013 --> 01:03:37,560
I refuse to be a hostage until my dying day.

647
01:03:37,563 --> 01:03:39,200
You must surpass Prince Nares.

648
01:03:39,263 --> 01:03:41,880
Hongsawadi must never fall to Ayutthaya.

649
01:03:42,050 --> 01:03:44,760
You are the Crown Prince of Hongsawadi.

650
01:03:44,851 --> 01:03:47,160
I am but a captive from Ayutthaya.

651
01:03:47,252 --> 01:03:48,760
How can we ever be brothers?
